WEBVTT

00:10.467 --> 00:11.465
<i> PREVIOUSLY ON "GREENLEAF"...</i>

00:11.467 --> 00:14.165
I KNOW YOU HAD AN AFFAIR
WITH LIONEL.

00:14.167 --> 00:15.565
THIS JUST
CAME FOR YOU, MA'AM.

00:15.567 --> 00:17.731
James: THE FIRST LADY
IS JOINING ME UP HERE TODAY

00:17.733 --> 00:19.798
BECAUSE WE HAVE
SOME NEWS TO SHARE.

00:19.800 --> 00:21.799
WE'RE DIVORCING.
[ GASPS ]

00:21.801 --> 00:23.432
YOU CAN HAVE THE HOUSE.

00:23.434 --> 00:24.998
I'LL TAKE CARE OF
THE IRS BILL,

00:25.000 --> 00:26.598
BUT YOU HAVE TO LEAVE
THE CHURCH.

00:26.600 --> 00:28.065
GRACE, I TRUST YOU.

00:28.067 --> 00:31.732
IF YOU SAY THAT THIS IS
THE CASE, THEN THIS IS THE CASE.

00:31.734 --> 00:33.498
WHAT ABOUT
MY SILVER JUBILEE?

00:33.500 --> 00:34.899
OH, YOU MEAN
THE SILVER JUBILEE

00:34.901 --> 00:37.098
THAT I WAS JUST INFORMED
ABOUT THIS MORNING?

00:37.100 --> 00:38.398
WHAT ABOUT IT?

00:38.400 --> 00:39.798
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
[ Sobbing ] LEAVE ME ALONE!

00:39.800 --> 00:42.065
STOP IT.
IT'S ALL LIES!

00:42.067 --> 00:45.198
WE WILL HAVE A VERY,
VERY SPECIAL GUEST --

00:45.200 --> 00:47.665
MAXINE PATTERSON.

00:47.667 --> 00:49.632
-YOU FOUND MORE CASH.
-YES.

00:49.634 --> 00:52.365
YOU EMPTIED
OUR SHARED ACCOUNT?

00:52.367 --> 00:54.165
IT'LL BE FULL
IN 2 WEEKS' TIME.

00:54.167 --> 00:56.332
IT'S TIME TO GO.

01:00.134 --> 01:04.598
<i> Man: [ Recorded voice]</i>
<i> CELEBRATING BISHOP JAMES</i>
<i> GREENLEAF'S SILVER JUBILEE,</i>

01:04.600 --> 01:09.498
<i> RECOGNIZING 25 YEARS OF SERVICE</i>
<i> AND DEDICATION TO THE COMMUNITY</i>

01:09.500 --> 01:12.098
<i> AND TO THE LORD'S CHURCH.</i>

01:12.100 --> 01:14.032
WOW.

01:14.034 --> 01:15.298
WHO'S HELPING YOU WITH THIS?

01:15.300 --> 01:16.965
NO ONE.

01:16.967 --> 01:19.699
CONTRARY TO POPULAR BELIEF,
I CAN RUN THIS CHURCH ON MY OWN.

01:19.701 --> 01:22.031
KARINE WAS SUPPOSED TO BE MY
AIDE-DE-CAMP THROUGH ALL THIS,

01:22.033 --> 01:25.665
BUT SHE'S SO BUSY WITH
YOUR MOTHER AND MAXINE'S TEAM

01:25.667 --> 01:28.498
THAT I [SCOFFS] I CAN'T
GET HER ATTENTION.

01:28.500 --> 01:30.131
Grace: BUT, DADDY, UH,
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE TO

01:30.133 --> 01:32.798
PUT A SYSTEM IN PLACE
FOR THIS EVENTUALLY.

01:32.800 --> 01:34.132
FOR WHAT?

01:34.134 --> 01:35.198
FOR HOW YOU'RE GOING TO HANDLE
STUFF LIKE THIS

01:35.200 --> 01:36.998
ON A REGULAR BASIS --

01:37.000 --> 01:41.532
DECORATIONS, FLOWERS, EVENTS,
MAKING THE CHURCH NICE.

01:41.534 --> 01:43.599
THE THINGS THAT MAMA
HAS ALWAYS DONE.

01:43.601 --> 01:45.198
I -- I THINK I'M DOING
A FINE JOB.

01:45.200 --> 01:48.598
YOU HAVE, FOR ONE SUNDAY,
BUT YOU, YOURSELF,

01:48.600 --> 01:50.665
SAID THE DAYS
GOT AWAY FROM YOU.

01:50.667 --> 01:53.465
YOU'RE GOING TO NEED
SOME HELP.

01:53.467 --> 01:55.065
DADDY?
MM-HMM.

01:55.067 --> 01:57.299
A BIT MUCH?

02:01.667 --> 02:02.932
YOU THINK?

02:05.400 --> 02:08.998
KARINE, WHAT AN UNEXPECTED
SURPRISE.

02:09.000 --> 02:11.199
MAE LET YOU OUT THE MINE?

02:13.000 --> 02:14.865
WHAT'S THIS?

02:14.867 --> 02:16.465
THE DIVORCE PAPERS.

02:16.467 --> 02:18.732
THEY WERE JUST COURIERED OVER
FROM THE LAWYERS.

02:18.734 --> 02:25.665
SO, UM, AFTER I SIGN THESE,
I'M A FREE MAN?

02:25.667 --> 02:27.899
ONCE SHE SIGNS THEM, TOO.

02:32.933 --> 02:35.131
FANTASTIC.

02:35.133 --> 02:37.732
[ SAD MUSIC PLAYS ]

02:37.734 --> 02:45.998
