07:09.533 --> 07:16.199
♪♪

07:16.201 --> 07:19.732
OH, LOOK AT THAT,
THE HAPPY FAMILY.

07:20.134 --> 07:21.865
[ LAUGHS ]

07:21.867 --> 07:24.332
HOW IS MY GRANDSON DOING?

07:24.334 --> 07:26.065
HE'S ALMOST FIGURED OUT
THE WALKING THING, BISHOP.

07:26.067 --> 07:27.865
LET ME SEE.
COME HERE, BABY.

07:27.867 --> 07:30.465
[ LAUGHS ]

07:30.467 --> 07:31.998
OOH.

07:32.000 --> 07:34.899
[ BABY CRIES ]

07:34.901 --> 07:36.832
OH.
ALL RIGHTY THEN.

07:36.834 --> 07:38.298
ALL RIGHTY.

07:38.300 --> 07:39.565
ALL RIGHTY.

07:39.567 --> 07:41.131
ALL RIGHT.
I GOT YOU, MAN.

07:41.133 --> 07:43.665
KEVIN.

07:43.667 --> 07:46.198
AARON.

07:46.200 --> 07:48.332
BYE, BABY.

07:48.334 --> 07:50.565
BYE, DADDY.

07:54.100 --> 07:56.065
BISHOP?

07:56.067 --> 07:57.732
HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

07:57.734 --> 07:59.732
MY DAD CALLED YOU
A FEW TIMES.

07:59.734 --> 08:01.332
OH, YES. HE HAS.

08:01.334 --> 08:02.998
YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN SO BUSY
WITH THE JUBILEE THAT I, UH...

08:03.000 --> 08:05.232
HE HAS PANCREATIC CANCER.

08:09.667 --> 08:12.465
I'M SORRY TO HEAR THAT.

08:12.467 --> 08:13.798
YEAH.

08:13.800 --> 08:16.265
HE'S DOING CHEMO
AT MEMPHIS GENERAL.

08:16.267 --> 08:17.732
THEY'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
THE BEST WHEN IT COMES

08:17.734 --> 08:20.665
TO THESE TYPE OF CANCERS.

08:20.667 --> 08:23.198
THEN YOU TWO
ARE ON SPEAKING TERMS?

08:23.200 --> 08:25.998
BARELY, BUT, YEAH.

08:26.000 --> 08:27.499
HE'S SICK.

08:29.800 --> 08:31.699
I'LL GIVE HIM A CALL.

08:34.201 --> 08:36.465
THANKS.

08:36.467 --> 08:42.865
♪♪

08:42.867 --> 08:49.332
♪♪

08:49.334 --> 08:55.865
♪♪

08:55.867 --> 09:02.132
♪♪

09:02.134 --> 09:08.665
♪♪

09:08.667 --> 09:11.031
COME IN.

09:11.033 --> 09:12.365
OH, HEY.

09:12.367 --> 09:15.632
YOU GOT A SECOND
FOR AN OLD MAN?

09:15.634 --> 09:18.098
GRANDPA, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

09:18.100 --> 09:20.198
JUST GOT OFF FROM WORK.

09:20.200 --> 09:22.265
I HOPE YOU DON'T THINK JUST
BECAUSE YOUR GRANDMOTHER

09:22.267 --> 09:23.865
AND I HAVE BEEN HAVING
OUR DIFFERENCES

09:23.867 --> 09:27.732
THAT I WILL NEVER VISIT.

09:27.734 --> 09:29.732
I GUESS I HOPE
THAT'S NOT THE CASE,

09:29.734 --> 09:33.332
BUT, YOU KNOW,
NOBODY KNOWS.

09:33.334 --> 09:38.299
I SEE THAT BIBLE I GAVE YOU
HAS BEEN OUT OF ROTATION LATELY.

09:40.567 --> 09:42.132
YEAH.

09:42.134 --> 09:45.132
I SHOULD PROBABLY
JUST GIVE IT BACK.

09:45.134 --> 09:47.798
NO, NO.
YOU HOLD ONTO IT FOR A WHILE.

09:47.800 --> 09:50.132
YOU NEVER KNOW WHEN
IT MIGHT COME IN HANDY.

09:50.134 --> 09:52.332
MAY I?

09:52.334 --> 09:55.399
SURE.

09:55.401 --> 10:01.532
I FEEL LIKE I SPEND MY WHOLE
LIFE IN THIS ROOM LATELY.

10:01.534 --> 10:06.065
BUT EVERY TIME I GO DOWNSTAIRS,
EVERYBODY JUST...

10:06.067 --> 10:08.965
I KNOW.
IT'S A CHORE, ISN'T IT,

10:08.967 --> 10:13.132
FIELDING EVERYONE'S CLUMSILY
STATED CONCERN?

10:13.134 --> 10:14.998
DO YOU EVER GET MAD?

10:15.000 --> 10:17.798
ABOUT WHAT,
HAVING PARKINSON'S?

10:17.800 --> 10:24.298
YEAH, AND EVERYTHING,
DYING.

10:24.300 --> 10:27.898
I USED TO, AT FIRST,
BUT YOU GET TO BE OLD

10:27.900 --> 10:29.565
AS ME, SOPHIA,
AND YOU COME TO REALIZE...

10:29.567 --> 10:34.065
AND I DON'T -- I DON'T MEAN
THIS TO SOUND TOO DEPRESSING.

10:34.067 --> 10:38.798
WE FALL APART, AND EVERYTHING
GETS TAKEN AWAY IN THE END,

10:38.800 --> 10:40.532
AND WHO WOULD I BLAME?

10:40.534 --> 10:43.265
GOD.

10:43.267 --> 10:48.131
FOR LETTING EVERYTHING
FALL APART IN THE FIRST PLACE.

10:48.133 --> 10:51.231
JUST COME TO CHURCH
ON SUNDAY.

10:51.233 --> 10:53.299
GRANDPA,
I DON'T WANT TO.

10:53.301 --> 10:56.965
IT JUST -- IT DOESN'T
FEEL RIGHT ANYMORE.

10:56.967 --> 11:02.398
I'M SORRY.
IT IS MY SILVER JUBILEE,

11:02.400 --> 11:05.532
AND I'LL TELL YOU SOMETHING
THAT YOU CAN'T TELL EVERYONE.

11:05.534 --> 11:08.965
GOD HAS GIVEN ME
A SPECIAL MESSAGE JUST FOR YOU.

11:11.400 --> 11:13.765
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

11:17.467 --> 11:19.032
I HATE MY LIFE.

11:21.267 --> 11:22.499
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

11:25.534 --> 11:27.732
YOU COME TO CHURCH.

11:27.734 --> 11:36.332
♪♪

11:36.334 --> 11:40.632
[ TRAIN HORN SOUNDS ]

11:41.534 --> 11:45.065
[ WHOOSH ]

11:45.067 --> 11:49.199
[ TRACKS CLICK-CLACKING ]

11:49.201 --> 11:57.332
♪♪

11:57.334 --> 12:05.299
♪♪

12:13.267 --> 12:16.998
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

12:17.000 --> 12:18.598
HEY.

12:18.600 --> 12:20.665
YOU MUST BE THE BISHOP.

12:22.734 --> 12:25.598
YOU MUST BE PERCY'S FRIEND.

12:25.600 --> 12:29.065
TERESA.

12:29.067 --> 12:30.932
JAMES.

12:30.934 --> 12:34.932
PERCY HAS TOLD ME
ALL ABOUT YOU.

12:34.934 --> 12:36.898
ALL GOOD, I HOPE?

12:36.900 --> 12:38.565
[ CHUCKLES ] MOSTLY.

12:38.567 --> 12:40.498
HE WISHES YOU WENT
A LITTLE EASIER ON YOURSELF,

12:40.500 --> 12:42.699
BUT THAT'S IT.

12:45.600 --> 12:49.265
IS, UM, IS PERCY AROUND?

12:49.267 --> 12:51.532
NO.
HE'S CONKED OUT.

12:51.534 --> 12:52.732
WE'RE DONE.

12:52.734 --> 12:57.265
OH.
I CAN STICK AROUND.

12:57.267 --> 12:59.798
OH, THANKS.

12:59.800 --> 13:01.798
I'M GOOD.

13:01.800 --> 13:03.965
ALL RIGHT THEN.

13:09.200 --> 13:11.399
BYE.

13:22.534 --> 13:24.399
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

13:24.401 --> 13:27.799
[ RADIO PLAYS ]

13:27.801 --> 13:29.932
THANKS FOR
COMING OVER, POP.

13:29.934 --> 13:32.198
WHERE'S KERISSA,
AT THE CHURCH TONIGHT?

13:32.200 --> 13:33.732
NO, SHE SAID SHE JUST
WANTED US

13:33.734 --> 13:36.932
TO HAVE SOME
FATHER-SON-GRANDSON TIME.

13:36.934 --> 13:39.932
PLUS, AT THIS POINT,
SHE'S NOT, UH,

13:39.934 --> 13:42.065
I'M NOT REALLY
ON HER GOOD SIDE.

13:42.067 --> 13:44.532
DON'T TELL ME
BECAUSE OF YOU AND TASHA.

13:44.534 --> 13:47.665
NO.
WHAT ABOUT ME AND TASHA?

13:47.667 --> 13:50.465
WELL, I CAME BY THE CHURCH
THE OTHER DAY.

13:50.467 --> 13:51.798
IT SEEMS TO ME THAT THE TWO
OF YOU

13:51.800 --> 13:54.265
WERE IN THE MIDDLE
OF SOMETHING.

13:54.267 --> 13:56.998
NO. THAT WAS --
THAT WAS NOTHING.

13:57.000 --> 13:59.265
I DON'T PLAY
THAT WAY ANYMORE, POP.

14:03.000 --> 14:04.999
GOOD.

14:05.001 --> 14:07.232
SO WHAT'D YOU WANT
TO TALK ABOUT?

14:11.267 --> 14:14.598
I GOT THE DIVORCE PAPERS
A FEW DAYS AGO.

14:14.600 --> 14:16.665
THEY'RE WAITING TO BE SIGNED.

14:16.667 --> 14:19.665
MAMA SIGN THEM YET?
NO.

14:19.667 --> 14:21.398
YOU HAVING DOUBTS?

14:21.400 --> 14:23.732
NO, NOT DOUBTS.

14:23.734 --> 14:27.932
IT'S COMPLICATED.

14:27.934 --> 14:30.699
I DON'T SEE ANY WAY FORWARD
THAT LOOKS RIGHT.

14:33.334 --> 14:35.599
GOD HASN'T GIVEN ME
ANY CLEAR PATH.

14:39.500 --> 14:42.398
IN THE MEANTIME, THOSE DIVORCE
PAPERS SIT IN MY BRIEFCASE,

14:42.400 --> 14:44.532
LIKE A BOMB.

14:46.934 --> 14:49.065
YOU DON'T WANT TO
SIGN THEM.

14:51.400 --> 14:53.465
THEN DON'T, POP.

14:56.000 --> 14:57.565
THEN WHAT?

14:57.567 --> 14:59.032
YOU HAVE YOUR JUBILEE.

14:59.034 --> 15:00.865
LET HER HAVE HER DAY.

15:00.867 --> 15:02.865
YOU TWO GO BACK TO
YOUR CORNERS.

15:02.867 --> 15:05.732
FIGHT IS OVER.

15:05.734 --> 15:07.065
YOU THINK THAT'S POSSIBLE?

15:07.067 --> 15:08.331
OH, I DO.

15:08.333 --> 15:10.499
YOU'RE NOT REALLY READY TO SIGN,
NOT YET.

15:15.200 --> 15:16.065
DO IT.

15:16.067 --> 15:18.732
SEE, I CAN'T DO IT.

15:18.734 --> 15:19.965
I CAN'T DO IT.

15:33.600 --> 15:35.032
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

15:37.834 --> 15:39.965
GOOD MORNING.

15:44.867 --> 15:46.665
SO HOW LONG HAS THIS PREACHER
FRIEND OF YOURS

15:46.667 --> 15:49.831
AND MAE BEEN HANGING OUT?

15:49.833 --> 15:51.632
I DON'T KNOW.

15:53.234 --> 15:55.198
MAE ALWAYS TAKES GREAT PAINS
TO MINIMIZE IT

15:55.200 --> 15:58.598
WHENEVER SHE SPEAKS OF IT.

15:58.600 --> 16:03.132
I ASSUME THAT'S TO MAKE
WHAT I DID SEEM EVEN WORSE.

16:03.134 --> 16:05.998
EITHER -- EITHER WAY,
IT HAPPENED.

16:06.000 --> 16:10.532
I THINK YOU SHOULD GO AHEAD
AND SPEAK TO HIM.

16:10.534 --> 16:12.465
WHY DO YOU SAY THAT?

16:12.467 --> 16:15.532
MOST FOLKS ONLY GET A FEW PEOPLE
YOU KNOW IN LIFE

16:15.534 --> 16:16.998
THAT THEY CAN
WORK THINGS OUT WITH,

16:17.000 --> 16:19.198
AND HE MIGHT BE ONE OF YOURS.

16:19.200 --> 16:29.065
♪♪

16:29.067 --> 16:30.765
I BROUGHT YOU
A CHARITY SPECIAL.

16:30.767 --> 16:34.832
[ Laughing ]
OH, THANK YOU.

16:34.834 --> 16:36.398
MM.
MM.

16:36.400 --> 16:37.732
MUST HAVE BEEN
READING MY MIND.

16:37.734 --> 16:40.132
NOW, YOU LOOKED LIKE YOU WERE
IN A BIT OF A STATE YESTERDAY,

16:40.134 --> 16:42.265
WHEN I SAW YOU.

16:42.267 --> 16:43.932
HMM?
I WAS.

16:43.934 --> 16:46.231
STILL AM, I GUESS.

16:46.233 --> 16:47.565
YOU WANT TO TALK ABOUT IT?

16:47.567 --> 16:50.332
KEVIN AND AARON
ARE BUYING A HOUSE.

16:50.334 --> 16:52.932
THEY WERE TELLING ME
RIGHT BEFORE YOU WALKED IN,

16:52.934 --> 16:55.198
MID-CENTURY.

16:55.200 --> 16:57.265
AND THEY'RE DOING THAT
AS A COUPLE?

16:57.267 --> 17:00.665
YEP, AND TALKING
ABOUT MARRIAGE.

17:00.667 --> 17:04.698
HMPH, THAT'S AWFULLY FAST,
ISN'T IT?

17:04.700 --> 17:09.265
I DON'T UNDERSTAND WHY EVERYBODY
GETS THEIR FAIRY-TALE

17:09.267 --> 17:12.365
ENDING EXCEPT FOR ME.

17:12.367 --> 17:14.298
YOU KNOW WHAT I DO WHEN I SEE
YOUR MOTHER

17:14.300 --> 17:16.032
MAKING HER PLANS THESE DAYS,

17:16.034 --> 17:19.865
COMING INTO HER OWN LIKE SHE
NEVER DID WHEN WE WERE TOGETHER?

17:19.867 --> 17:20.932
WHAT?

17:20.934 --> 17:23.265
I PLAY YOUR CD.

17:23.267 --> 17:28.298
I WATCH JACOB PREACH
ON THE TRIUMPH WEBSITE.

17:28.300 --> 17:31.332
I OPEN THE PAPER,
AND I SEE WHAT HOLY RUCKUS

17:31.334 --> 17:33.599
THAT SISTER OF YOURS
HAS MADE TODAY,

17:33.601 --> 17:38.398
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

17:38.400 --> 17:41.798
AND I THANK GOD
FOR THE THREE OF YOU

17:41.800 --> 17:46.465
AND FOR THE WOMAN
WHO RAISED YOU ALL WITH ME.

17:46.467 --> 17:49.532
THE HAPPIER KEVIN GETS...

17:49.534 --> 17:55.998
AND WE HAVE TO ASSUME THAT
HE WAS UNHAPPY FOR A LONG TIME

17:56.000 --> 18:00.665
...WELL,
THE BETTER IT IS FOR NATHAN,

18:00.667 --> 18:04.332
AND THAT'S WHAT MATTERS.
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:04.334 --> 18:06.265
I KNOW. [ SNIFFS ]
RIGHT?

18:06.267 --> 18:09.865
I KNOW.
YOU'RE RIGHT.

18:09.867 --> 18:12.899
NOW, WHAT YOU SINGING
FOR ME ON SUNDAY?

18:15.767 --> 18:18.398
"IF I CAN HELP SOMEBODY."

18:18.400 --> 18:19.665
MY FAVORITE SONG.

18:19.667 --> 18:21.332
I KNOW, DADDY.

18:21.334 --> 18:22.531
OH, MIND IF I JOIN YOU?

18:22.533 --> 18:23.999
IT IS MY SILVER JUBILEE.

18:24.001 --> 18:25.998
DO I HAVE A CHOICE?

18:26.000 --> 18:31.798
♪ James: OH, MY LIVING ♪

18:31.800 --> 18:33.132
♪ MY LIVING ♪

18:33.134 --> 18:36.265
♪ SHALL NOT BE ♪

18:36.267 --> 18:38.231
♪ SHALL NOT BE ♪

18:38.233 --> 18:40.498
♪ IN VAIN ♪

18:40.500 --> 18:47.598
♪ HEY, HEY ♪

18:47.600 --> 18:50.132
♪ IF I ♪

18:50.134 --> 18:52.932
♪ IF I ♪
♪ CAN HELP SOMEBODY ♪

18:55.733 --> 19:01.132
♪ AS I'M SINGING,
SINGING THIS SONG ♪

19:04.234 --> 19:08.732
Both: ♪ MY LIVING ♪

19:08.734 --> 19:17.132
♪ SHALL NOT BE IN VAIN ♪

19:17.134 --> 19:20.532
♪ NO WAY ♪

19:20.534 --> 19:21.998
♪ THANK YOU, JESUS ♪

19:22.000 --> 19:26.332
♪ MY LIVING ♪
♪ MY LIVING ♪

19:26.334 --> 19:30.932
♪ SHALL NOT ♪

19:30.934 --> 19:36.265
♪ BE IN VAIN ♪

19:36.267 --> 19:39.665
♪ HALLELUJAH ♪

19:39.667 --> 19:42.565
[ CHATTER AND APPLAUSE ]

19:50.267 --> 19:53.532
[ APPLAUSE STOPS ]

19:53.534 --> 19:55.998
-MORNING, CAVALRY.
-MORNING.

19:56.000 --> 19:58.565
NOW THAT WAS SOME GOOD SINGING,
DADDY.

19:58.567 --> 20:00.298
YOU GIVE HIM ANOTHER HAND.

20:00.300 --> 20:04.298
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

20:04.300 --> 20:07.065
AMEN.

20:07.067 --> 20:10.265
NOW WHAT CAN I SAY
ABOUT MY FATHER,

20:10.267 --> 20:12.798
BY WAY OF INTRODUCTION,
THIS MORNING, HMM?

20:12.800 --> 20:18.132
BY WAY OF CELEBRATION,
REALLY BY WAY OF REVELATION.

20:18.134 --> 20:20.731
SOME OF Y'ALL HAVE KNOWN HIM
LONGER THAN I HAVE.

20:20.733 --> 20:22.065
Woman: AMEN.

20:22.067 --> 20:25.665
NOW WHAT I WANT TO TALK
ABOUT THIS MORNING IS THIS.

20:27.934 --> 20:32.465
MY DADDY, MY BISHOP,
<i> YOUR</i> BISHOP...

20:32.467 --> 20:33.865
-THAT'S RIGHT.
-YES.

20:33.867 --> 20:36.398
...IS A MAN OF FAITH.

20:36.400 --> 20:38.598
Woman: YES.

20:38.600 --> 20:40.265
[ APPLAUSE ]

20:41.400 --> 20:44.099
HE DOESN'T WALK BY SIGHT.

20:44.101 --> 20:48.098
NOW DO I WISH SOMETIMES THAT
HE WAS A LITTLE LESS TRUSTING,

20:48.100 --> 20:50.865
A LITTLE MORE CAREFUL?
[ LAUGHS ] YEAH.

20:50.867 --> 20:54.198
I DO, BUT I HAVE GROWN MORE
IN THE LIGHT

20:54.200 --> 20:56.265
OF MY FATHER'S FAITH IN ME,

20:56.267 --> 21:00.998
SO WHO AM I TO DENY
SOMEONE ELSE THAT ADVANTAGE?

21:01.000 --> 21:07.998
WE ALL OWE SO MUCH TO THE FAITH
THE BISHOP HAS HAD IN US.

21:08.000 --> 21:11.732
IT'S ONLY FITTING THAT WE
REAFFIRM OUR FAITH IN HIM

21:11.734 --> 21:14.732
AND WELCOME HIM TO THE PULPIT
WITH HOLY ENTHUSIASM.

21:14.734 --> 21:16.165
NOW I WANT YOU TO GET UP.
-ALL RIGHT NOW.

21:16.167 --> 21:19.665
Grace: I WANT YOU TO GET
EXCITED, GIVING GLORY TO GOD.

21:19.667 --> 21:24.732
WELCOME BISHOP
JAMES GREENLEAF.

21:24.734 --> 21:32.265
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

21:32.267 --> 21:35.132
ROCHELLE IS NOT
WHAT YOU THINK.

21:35.134 --> 21:37.365
I HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.

21:42.000 --> 21:45.565
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE
INTENSIFY ]

21:48.300 --> 21:50.499
AMEN.

21:53.400 --> 21:55.031
GOOD SERMON, BISHOP.

21:55.033 --> 21:56.899
WELL, THANK YOU
FOR SAYING SO.

21:56.901 --> 21:59.499
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TRICKS MAE AND
MAXINE HAVE UP THEIR SLEEVES,

21:59.501 --> 22:01.032
BUT<i> THAT'S</i> GOING TO BE
HARD TO BEAT.

22:01.034 --> 22:02.698
IT'S NOT A COMPETITION,
CONNIE.

22:02.700 --> 22:06.532
YES. IT IS.
SOPHIA.

22:06.534 --> 22:09.665
WELL, WHAT'D YOU THINK?

22:09.667 --> 22:11.465
YOUR SPIRIT DIDN'T HEAR THAT?

22:11.467 --> 22:13.065
I DON'T
THINK I HAVE A SPIRIT.

22:13.067 --> 22:14.798
DON'T EVEN
THINK THAT THOUGHT.

22:14.800 --> 22:17.065
CAN YOU COME TO MY OFFICE?
NO.

22:17.067 --> 22:19.132
I'M GOING TO GO HOME AND GET
THAT BIBLE THAT YOU GAVE ME.

22:19.134 --> 22:23.598
SOPHIA GREENLEAF, GIVE ME
10 MINUTES, 10 MINUTES, 5.

22:23.600 --> 22:25.065
AND WHAT?

22:25.067 --> 22:27.532
I'M GOING TO TELL YOU
THE MEANING OF LIFE.

22:27.534 --> 22:32.665
♪♪

22:32.667 --> 22:38.598
SIT HERE BECAUSE I WANT YOU
TO SEE THAT NOTHING

22:38.600 --> 22:42.732
IS ANY CLEARER BEHIND THAT DESK
THAN IT IS ANYWHERE ELSE.

22:42.734 --> 22:44.965
OKAY?

22:47.201 --> 22:51.065
NOW THIS IS WHAT I WANT
TO TELL YOU.

22:51.067 --> 22:55.998
YOU'RE BORN, AND BY THE TIME
YOU'RE 5, 6,

22:56.000 --> 23:00.731
YOU LOOK AROUND AND YOU REALIZE
THAT YOU'RE ON A TRAIN.

23:00.733 --> 23:03.265
AND BY THE TIME YOU'RE YOUR AGE,
YOU REALIZE,

23:03.267 --> 23:07.065
OH, WELL, THAT TRAIN
IS GOING VERY FAST,

23:07.067 --> 23:08.865
FASTER THAN ANYTHING
YOU'VE EVER READ ABOUT,

23:08.867 --> 23:10.265
ANYTHING YOU'VE EVER SEEN.

23:10.267 --> 23:13.099
SO YOU SEE YOUR PARENTS,
AND YOU ASK THEM,

23:13.101 --> 23:15.298
"ARE WE ON A RUNAWAY TRAIN?"

23:15.300 --> 23:20.332
AND THEY SAY, "NO. NO.
WE WOULD NEVER DO THAT TO YOU,

23:20.334 --> 23:22.132
BRING YOU INTO A WORLD
WE CAN'T CONTROL,

23:22.134 --> 23:23.798
THAT NO ONE CAN CONTROL."

23:23.800 --> 23:25.332
BUT THAT'S EXACTLY
HOW IT IS.

23:25.334 --> 23:27.132
SO YOU SAY, "I'M GOING TO GO
TO THE FRONT.

23:27.134 --> 23:28.132
I'M GOING TO TALK
TO THE ENGINEER.

23:28.134 --> 23:29.398
THERE'S GOT TO BE ONE."

23:29.400 --> 23:33.332
YOU GO TO THE FRONT,

23:33.334 --> 23:37.731
BUT BY THE TIME
YOU GET THERE, YOU'RE ANGRY.

23:37.733 --> 23:39.331
WHY?

23:39.333 --> 23:42.065
BECAUSE BY THE TIME YOU GET
TO THE FRONT, YOU'VE SEEN

23:42.067 --> 23:48.699
THAT THIS WHOLE TRAIN
IS FILLED WITH SCARED PEOPLE.

23:48.701 --> 23:53.698
YOU BANG ON THE DOOR,
AND YOU SAY, "OPEN THIS DOOR.

23:53.700 --> 23:55.265
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU,"

23:55.267 --> 23:59.498
AND BY THE TIME
YOU KICK DOWN THAT DOOR,

23:59.500 --> 24:05.365
AND YOU SEE --
YOU SEE THE ENGINEER'S FACE,

24:05.367 --> 24:09.699
AND YOU CAN SEE THE TEARS
IN HIS EYES,

24:11.867 --> 24:16.198
THAT HE KNOWS EXACTLY
WHAT'S GOING ON.

24:16.200 --> 24:19.898
HE FEELS ALL THE PAIN
THAT YOU FEEL,

24:19.900 --> 24:23.598
ALL THE FEAR, EVERYBODY'S,

24:23.600 --> 24:28.798
AND HE'S DOING EVERYTHING
HE CAN TO MAKE IT BETTER.

24:28.800 --> 24:33.932
SO YOU SAY, "HOW CAN I HELP?"

24:33.934 --> 24:35.998
HE SAYS, "WHO ARE YOU?"

24:36.000 --> 24:44.765
YOU SAY, "I -- I'M SOPHIA,"
OR, "I'M JAMES," AND HE SAYS,

24:47.334 --> 24:55.132
"GO BACK THERE, SOPHIA,
PLEASE, AND YOU --

24:55.134 --> 25:00.665
YOU TELL EVERYBODY
THAT I LOVE THEM,

25:03.600 --> 25:07.132
AND I'M DOING THE BEST
THAT I CAN TO BRING THIS THING

25:07.134 --> 25:11.498
TO A SAFE
AND SATISFYING END,

25:11.500 --> 25:18.031
AND IF YOU EVER WANT TO TALK,
YOU KNOW WHERE TO FIND ME,"

25:18.033 --> 25:21.965
SO YOU GO BACK INTO THE TRAIN,

25:21.967 --> 25:24.199
AND YOU LIVE
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.

25:28.734 --> 25:30.965
THAT'S IT.

25:33.101 --> 25:35.431
THAT'S LIFE.

25:35.433 --> 25:38.965
THAT'S SALVATION.

25:38.967 --> 25:44.265
HAPPINESS ISN'T
THE ABSENT OF SADNESS.

25:44.267 --> 25:49.798
IT'S LIVING, AND IT'S BEING
IN THE MYSTERY

25:49.800 --> 25:56.598
AND THE ADVENTURE OF THIS LIFE
IN GOD'S WORLD WITH OTHERS,

25:56.600 --> 25:59.332
WITH GOD.

25:59.334 --> 26:01.465
I KNOW THAT YOU,

26:01.467 --> 26:06.065
YOU FEEL THAT GOD
IS NOT THERE FOR YOU RIGHT NOW,

26:06.067 --> 26:13.198
BUT I NEED YOU TO KNOW THAT
YOU NEED TO BE THERE FOR GOD.

26:13.200 --> 26:15.299
GOD NEEDS YOU.

26:19.367 --> 26:21.032
[ GRUNTS ]

26:21.034 --> 26:30.065
♪♪

26:30.067 --> 26:33.198
I JUST WANT YOU
TO BE HAPPY AGAIN.

26:33.200 --> 26:35.598
I WANT TO SEE THAT SMILE
ON YOUR FACE.

26:35.600 --> 26:41.265
♪♪

26:41.267 --> 26:43.132
BYE.

26:43.134 --> 26:45.365
LOVE YOU, GRANDPA.

26:46.134 --> 26:49.398
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

26:49.400 --> 26:57.398
♪♪

26:57.400 --> 27:05.232
♪♪

27:15.867 --> 27:17.932
ALL ALONE TONIGHT, PERCY?

27:21.067 --> 27:26.932
WELL, I, UH, I CAN'T AFFORD

27:26.934 --> 27:29.765
THIS KIND OF ACTION
MORE THAN ONCE A WEEK.

27:29.767 --> 27:32.131
WHAT DO YOU SPEND
YOUR MONEY ON?

27:32.133 --> 27:33.665
I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT MONEY,
JAMES.

27:33.667 --> 27:39.365
I'M TALKING ABOUT --
I'M TALKING ABOUT SELF-RESPECT.

27:39.367 --> 27:43.965
HMM. HMM.

27:43.967 --> 27:49.198
NO MATTER HOW GOOD
THOSE WOMEN ACT,

27:49.200 --> 27:53.398
YOU DON'T EVER FORGET
THAT YOU'RE PAYING FOR IT.

27:53.400 --> 27:56.132
YOU'VE GOT SUCH A RARE THING
WITH ROCHELLE.

27:58.600 --> 28:02.265
HMM, YOUNG WOMAN LIKE THAT,

28:04.800 --> 28:09.898
ALL READY TO RUB YOUR FEET,
RIDE YOU.

28:09.900 --> 28:15.265
MAN, I'M JUST TELLING YOU ABOUT
HOW RARE THAT THING IS, JAMES,

28:15.267 --> 28:19.265
AND NOW AN UNBELIEVABLE
GOOD NIGHT.

28:19.267 --> 28:25.065
♪♪

28:25.067 --> 28:31.065
♪♪

28:31.067 --> 28:36.932
♪♪

28:36.934 --> 28:42.798
♪♪

28:42.800 --> 28:48.798
♪♪

28:48.800 --> 28:54.598
♪♪

28:54.600 --> 29:00.598
♪♪

29:00.600 --> 29:06.398
♪♪

29:06.400 --> 29:12.332
♪♪

29:12.334 --> 29:18.332
♪♪

29:18.334 --> 29:24.132
♪♪

29:24.134 --> 29:26.365
Rochelle:
IS SOMETHING WRONG?

29:28.600 --> 29:30.198
I'M NOT SURE.

29:30.200 --> 29:32.465
DOES IT HAVE TO DO
WITH THE INVESTMENTS?

29:32.467 --> 29:34.665
OH, NO. NO. NO.
IT'S NOT THAT.

29:34.667 --> 29:37.065
GOOD, BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,
THOSE TAKE TIME.

29:37.067 --> 29:39.865
YOU HAVE TO HAVE PATIENCE.

29:39.867 --> 29:41.531
MM.

29:41.533 --> 29:44.165
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN MY LIFE?

29:44.167 --> 29:45.698
WHAT DO YOU THINK I'M DOING?

29:45.700 --> 29:49.132
I DON'T KNOW.

29:49.134 --> 29:52.665
I MEAN, I THOUGHT I KNEW,
BUT NOW I'M JUST --

29:52.667 --> 29:55.998
I'M -- I'M NOT SURE.

29:56.000 --> 29:58.165
YOU SAY YOU LOVE ME.

30:01.534 --> 30:03.999
IS THAT TRUE?

30:04.001 --> 30:06.131
WHY WOULD I SAY IT
IF I DIDN'T MEAN IT?

30:06.133 --> 30:09.932
I DON'T KNOW.

30:09.934 --> 30:12.631
LOOK AT ME.

30:12.633 --> 30:14.231
LOOK AT ME, I'M...
I'M LOOKING AT YOU.

30:14.233 --> 30:16.765
I'M AN OLD MAN.

30:16.767 --> 30:18.899
MY HANDS SHAKE.

30:22.101 --> 30:26.098
MY BODY IS NOT WHAT IT USED TO
BE, AND IT NEVER WILL BE AGAIN.

30:26.100 --> 30:28.965
NOW, IN A CITY FULL OF YOUNG
STUDS TO CHOOSE FROM,

30:31.134 --> 30:35.098
WHAT DO YOU WANT WITH ME?

30:35.100 --> 30:38.332
YOU THINK I'M USING YOU
OR SOMETHING?

30:38.334 --> 30:40.132
HMM?
I DON'T KNOW.

30:40.134 --> 30:43.532
TO WHAT, HELP OUT
WITH MY LACK OF HEARTACHE

30:43.534 --> 30:47.132
OR MY LACK OF HEADACHE?

30:47.134 --> 30:49.265
TAKE OUT YOUR PHONE.

30:51.667 --> 30:52.998
OPEN UP THAT APP
I SHOWED YOU,

30:53.000 --> 30:55.665
THE ONE THAT SHOWS YOU
ALL YOUR ACCOUNTS.

30:55.667 --> 31:05.598
♪♪

31:05.600 --> 31:07.398
HOLY GOD IN HEAVEN.

31:07.400 --> 31:11.265
NOW WHO IS USING WHO, HMM?

31:11.267 --> 31:13.131
HAVE I MADE
THAT MUCH ALREADY?

31:13.133 --> 31:18.332
I SAID, "WHO IS USING WHO?"
JAMES.

31:18.334 --> 31:20.798
YOU'RE MAKING MONEY ALREADY.

31:20.800 --> 31:22.932
BUT WHAT I GOT?

31:22.934 --> 31:26.865
NO MAN, NO RING, NOTHING.

31:26.867 --> 31:28.331
ARE YOU USING ME?
NO.

31:28.333 --> 31:29.399
BECAUSE THAT'S WHAT
IT SEEMS LIKE.

31:29.401 --> 31:30.998
NO, NO.
YEAH.

31:31.000 --> 31:33.932
I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY I ASKED THE QUESTION.

31:33.934 --> 31:36.132
I'M SO TIRED
OF YOUR ENTIRE FAMILY.

31:36.134 --> 31:38.265
ALL OF Y'ALL ARE SNAKES.

31:40.534 --> 31:45.099
ALL Y'ALL SEE IS SNAKES,
AND I'M OVER IT.

31:48.467 --> 31:50.331
ROCHELLE.
ROCHELLE.

31:50.333 --> 31:51.399
NO.
I'M SERIOUS, JAMES.

31:51.401 --> 31:52.799
YOU KNOW,
YOU JUST GO AHEAD ON

31:52.801 --> 31:55.532
AND TAKE CARE OF YOUR IRS BILL.
ALL RIGHT?

31:55.534 --> 31:56.998
I'M GLAD I COULD BE
OF SOME ASSISTANCE.

31:57.000 --> 31:59.232
ROCHELLE,
PLEASE DON'T GO.

32:01.600 --> 32:03.799
I'LL NEVER
DOUBT YOU AGAIN.

32:06.067 --> 32:09.465
PLEASE.

32:09.467 --> 32:11.499
PLEASE.

32:25.767 --> 32:30.065
[ TRAIN HORN SOUNDS ]

32:30.067 --> 32:32.165
Percy: YOU GO AND SEE
THAT LIONEL YET?

32:34.334 --> 32:36.432
I'LL GO TODAY.

32:40.000 --> 32:42.198
GOOD.

32:42.200 --> 32:51.132
♪♪

32:51.134 --> 32:53.232
Man: LIONEL JEFFRIES?

32:53.234 --> 32:59.065
♪♪

32:59.067 --> 33:00.865
[ SIGHS HEAVILY ]

33:00.867 --> 33:10.865
♪♪

33:10.867 --> 33:20.732
♪♪

33:20.734 --> 33:26.399
UM, MA'AM,
I'M BISHOP GREENLEAF.

33:26.401 --> 33:30.432
ARE YOU OKAY?

33:30.434 --> 33:32.632
HAVE YOU LOST A LOVED ONE?

33:32.634 --> 33:34.965
NO.

33:34.967 --> 33:36.899
IF THERE'S ANYTHING
I CAN DO...

33:40.734 --> 33:43.198
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND
IF I --

33:43.200 --> 33:46.398
IF I JUST SIT WITH YOU
FOR A WHILE.

33:46.400 --> 33:48.599
[ Shakily ] IT'S OKAY.

33:53.500 --> 33:55.699
[ Voice breaks ]
IT'S MY FATHER.

33:58.667 --> 34:01.865
IT'S HIS LEFT HIP, AND HE
DOESN'T KNOW ANYBODY HERE,

34:01.867 --> 34:05.932
AND I CAN'T
TAKE CARE OF HIM.

34:05.934 --> 34:08.065
HMM.

34:08.067 --> 34:10.798
I HAVE KIDS.
[ SNIFFS ]

34:10.800 --> 34:14.798
I, UH, HAVE TO WORK,

34:14.800 --> 34:18.499
AND I CAN'T
WATCH HIM ALL THE TIME.

34:20.800 --> 34:24.398
THANK YOU.

34:24.400 --> 34:28.332
HE NEEDS SOMEONE
THAT CAN FEED HIM,

34:28.334 --> 34:34.265
YOU KNOW, AND BATHE HIM.

34:34.267 --> 34:36.599
I TRIED.
I TRIED REALLY HARD, I DID.

34:36.601 --> 34:41.799
WHAT A BLESSING THAT GOD
GAVE YOU A FATHER

34:41.801 --> 34:45.632
THAT MEANS SO MUCH TO YOU,

34:45.634 --> 34:49.532
AND THAT YOU'RE ABLE
TO DEMONSTRATE THAT LOVE

34:49.534 --> 34:54.265
BY GIVING HIM THE BEST CARE
THAT YOU CAN GIVE,

34:54.267 --> 34:56.198
BY PUTTING HIM HERE.

34:56.200 --> 35:00.499
GOD KNOWS THAT YOU TRYING
TO DO IT YOURSELF

35:02.934 --> 35:06.132
WOULDN'T BE
IN ANYBODY'S BEST INTEREST,

35:06.134 --> 35:11.132
NOT YOUR FATHER'S,
NOT YOURS OR YOUR FAMILY'S.

35:11.134 --> 35:16.032
THIS, WHAT YOU'RE DOING,
IS A PURE ACT OF LOVE.

35:18.133 --> 35:21.332
YEAH, BUT THIS LOVE HURTS.

35:24.000 --> 35:26.065
CAN WE PRAY TOGETHER?

35:28.934 --> 35:34.265
MAY THE BLESSINGS OF GOD
BE UPON YOU ALWAYS.

35:34.267 --> 35:37.732
AMEN.

35:37.734 --> 35:39.865
THANK YOU.

35:45.934 --> 35:48.132
Man: COME IN.

35:48.134 --> 35:54.232
♪♪

35:54.234 --> 35:55.865
[ SIGHS ]

35:55.867 --> 36:02.198
♪♪

36:02.200 --> 36:04.998
THANK YOU FOR COMING.

36:05.000 --> 36:06.132
YOU HAVE SOMETHING TO SAY?

36:06.134 --> 36:09.232
I -- I ASSUME
THAT'S WHY YOU CALLED.

36:11.467 --> 36:13.598
I JUST WANT TO SAY
I'M SORRY.

36:13.600 --> 36:22.832
♪♪

36:22.834 --> 36:27.099
I DON'T EXPECT THAT
YOU WILL FORGIVE ME.

36:27.101 --> 36:33.032
A MAN EXPECTS HIS DEALINGS
WITH A WOMAN TO BE SPLINTERED,

36:33.034 --> 36:37.932
FRAUGHT, MESSY, IMPRECISE,

36:37.934 --> 36:40.865
BUT HE LOOKS TO HIS FRIENDS
TO KEEP THINGS WHOLE.

36:44.800 --> 36:49.598
I AM SO SORRY, JAMES.

36:49.600 --> 36:52.831
WHAT WAS DONE WAS WRONG
